@anchor{batch_answers_from_file}
@defvr {Option variable} batch_answers_from_file
Default value: @code{false}

If @code{true}, then @code{batch} reads answers to interactive questions
from its input file or stream.

Example: Maxima's interactive testsuite includes something like
following.

@example
[asksign (foo), sign (foo), sign (foo)];
p;
[pos, pos, pos];
@end example

The first line makes Maxima ask a question; when
@code{batch_answers_from_file} is @code{true}, the second line is read
as the answer to the question; and the third line provides the expected
result.

The command-line option @code{--batch-string} binds
@code{batch_answers_from_file} to @code{true}. The @code{run_testsuite}
function, as a default, also binds @code{batch_answers_from_file} to
@code{true}. @mref{command_line_options} and @mrefdot{run_testsuite}

